team-page-text:
Google is known all around the world. Everyone is 'googling', checking on 'maps' and communicating in 'gmail'. For simple users, these are services that just work. For us developers its more: APIs, scalability issues, complex technology stacks, usability and design. And that is what Google Developer Groups are about.

The GDGs and Woman Techmakers of Hamburg are open, volunteer-based geek communities creating exciting projects and events to share their knowledge and passion about Google technologies.
